history.content:
I saw a Piazza post saying that 194-38 is approved as an upper div.

See @3930 for using graduate courses for upper division credit. Talk with an adviser about the upper-div situation, but probably not.

children.subject: This is fairly common. Just take another course.
Thanks, good to confirm 194-38 counts. Does anyone (preferably an adviser) know about the 1 unit situation?

history.content: Student answer below is correct. If you do not reach 20 units, you would need to take another course. Keep in mind that many students take more than the required 20 units anyway.

I just wanted to double check about some classes and whether they count for the 20 units of upper div CS credit. I spoke to an advisor a while ago and she had said 194-38 (Cyberwar) would count as an upper div, is this still true? I wanted to check because I saw someone on piazza say it was not. 
I also wanted to ask about CS 261, the graduate security course. Would this count as one of my upper div CS courses? It's a 3 unit course too, so if it did count I would only have 19 upper div CS units. Is there any class/something I can take to get that last unit without having to take a whole other 4 unit upper div?
Thanks
history.subject: Courses counting for upper div CS credit
